If you love home made Mexican food, eat here. I had the beef burrito with a side salad of lettuce, tomatoes, & avocado. The dressing was fresh lime wedges--yes!! I also shared fresh flour tortilla chips with guacamole with my friends--delicious!! Their menu is big so there is something for most people. I would give them five stars if they offered organic choices. Also, it really isn't handicap-friendly.  There is one giant step you need to climb to enter the restaurant. Once inside it's a tight squeeze to get a rollator thru to a table. A motorized scooter won't make it. A wheelchair is iffy. The good news the majority if their business is takeout & home delivery--yay!🎉

This place is one of the best spots in New York City hands down. I've been so several all over and none comepare to this place and one other on Nostrand, they are titans of the Mexican cuisine. My pictures are horchata, Chips and guacamole with a size of extra guac, Chicken Flautas and a Steak Chimichanga meal. I normally can't pass up steak or chick Tostadas but today I did. Have fun finding what you love best.

If you do not speak Spanish, I would avoid this place. Me and my wife walked in at 6, we were handed menus, and were never spoken to again. We waited 45 minutes with no water or anything. I watched a little Spanish speaking lady walk in and get a menu, drink and her order in within 10 minutes. She walked in 30 minutes after us... Every time our young, terrible, racist waitress wearing an all black outfit walked passed us to give service to other people, she would lock eye contact with me and passively aggressively look down. So eventually we walked out. She even walked by us as we were walking out, she accidentally made another awkward eye contact, and once again passively aggressively look down and brisk past to give service to the people that were worth it. The thing is, I could care less if you only serve Spanish speaking people, just put a sign out front if that’s the case, don’t let me sit there all day wasting my time for no reason. So again, unless you speak Spanish, because your a hassle if you don’t, I would avoid this place like the plague. Unless you like sitting at a table, staring at your partner with an empty stomach, in that case, I would highly recommend this terrible place. FYI my wife appears white but actually speaks very fluent Spanish.....

AY CARAMBA!! This place is fantastic! Walked in and placed an order and within five minutes started my walk back to my apartment. The taqueria itself is really quaint and homey. Lots of Central American artwork gives it a true authentic feel while you sink your teeth into the overflowing tacos. I couldn't even find my tortillas in my to-go box because of how STUFFED  these were. Two great sauces were included, a classic verde style salsa and the other a guacamole based sauce.  I can't express it enough how great this place is. I highly recommend getting their tacos to start off your new and improved Taqueria experience and slowly venture to new parts of the menu from there.
